<font color="#FF0000">WAR</font><br>
<tt>Wed Jan  7  8:54:02 US/Eastern 1998
</tt><p>
I once asked my daughter what she thought about her high school history class.  She told me that the history of the world is the history of war.  I told her that history was more than war, but she made her point.<br><br>
I told her that America is, more than a country, it is an experiement in freedom -- and that freedom is a value and a goal that should not be taken lightly.  It is important to the human condition.  Most people understand that fact.<br><br>
Wars are fought for a variety of reasons -- economic, idealogical and personal to name a few.  War is certainly not impressive, but I think that many times we have not yet learned how to avoid it in some cirucmstances.  I think the world is getting better, but we still have a long way to go in learning to live and let live.<br><br>
Paul
